<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98317518928528></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98317518928528><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=98317518928528>RE: Dark Elf or Iksar 2 -- or Erudite- the first one got sor</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=98317518928528#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 26th 3:13 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you want int, go Erudite.  You'll have a bigger gas tank.<br><br>Pros:  <br><br>* Int.  Huge int.  You can get to 200 without planes gear, and still have some slots for other stats such as direct modifiers of mana.  In a long fight, you'll still often wind up with plenty of reserve.<br><br>* Paineel newbie area rocks.  All decay skels all the time.  The chips you get now will keep you stocked until 20 or so. <br><br>* Welcome almost everywhere.  DE NPCs appreciate us as practitioners of the True Art.  Goodies put up with us because we're not an evil race.<br><br>Cons: Nightblind.  No Iksar regen.<br><br>For nightblindness, change your monitor settings.  My Erudite can see well enough now, but when I started the game I didn't realize my monitor brightness was turned down.  My DE couldn't see the path under her feet at night unless I had the lights off in the room.  And you get summon coldstone, so you're never completely in the dark even on corpse retrieval.<br><br><br>If you want higher sustained output, go Iksar. <br><br>Pros:<br><br>* Regen. You can run your lich spell longer before having to slow med the rest of the way to readiness.  When kills are fast, and you can leave your lich on all the time no matter what race, you spend more mana on harder-hitting nukes and dots and less on draining back the hp you spent on lich.<br><br>* That other stuff.  AC, who cares?  If a necro is getting hit, a necro is getting dead.  What matters is whether you regain concentration, not what your AC is.  Get ac gear on your erudite instead of int gear, and I bet you'll make up the difference in AC before you make up the difference in int.<br><br>Cons: KOS, low int, xp penalty.<br><br>If you want to roleplay classic evil, go for a DE.  <br><br>Their int is ok, and they can make themselves welcome by killing the local pests (orcs, gnolls, goblins).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
