	   <tr><td colspan=2>I personally chose an Erudite necro (two of them in fact... one reached lvl 18 before I restarted, and the other is now lvl 28) and I would not change a thing.<br><br>Erudites have phenominal faction:<br>I am welcome in Paineel, Erudin, Qeynos(after killing one level worth of gnolls from 7 to 8), Highpass(after killing one level of orcs from 21 to 22), the Karanas, the bridge between north & south karana, Neriak, Freeport, Felwithe, Kelethin(except rangers and druids) ... basically what this means, is that I have free travel all over. I am KOS to Firona Vie, but I can use the outpost in Overthere.<br><br>my base intel was 142, and consiering that intel is where your mana comes from, I'm glad it was so high. I have the disadvantage of not seeing in the dark quite as well as a DE, but at lvl 4 you get the "Deadeye" spell and it remedies that anyway. Then at lvl 24, you get Shadow Sight which is ultravision anyway.<br><br>The hunting in Paineel and Tox forest was excellent until about lvl 8, at which time you can invis and make the trip to Qeynos and do blackburrow... and there is the Qeynos Aquaducts where you can do banking, training and spell buying there.<br><br>Some people don't care about their factions and they would rather just build up intel through items, and that is their choice... but personally, I like having the abillity to travel all around freely and knowing that if I were wearing all the same items as many other necros I would have a higher intel and thus more mana....<br><br>just my two cents and IMHO of coures.<br><br>Khrystia Soulburner<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
